page.title: 10Landscape north: FINTRY
page.content: This is an area of dramatic changes in scenery. The many{lava flows}which make up the high ground contrast markedly with the low lying{glacial {deposits}on top of the softer { {sedimentary rocks.}Stronend (629.895) is a noted glacial site featuring successive layers of rocks. East of Culcreuch House is a{volcanic plug. { The ice which moved from Loch Lomond through the Endrick valley has left { {striations}on the higher ground where the rock is exposed. On lower ground the {boulder clay}has been formed into {drumlins. { Large deposits of lake bed material have been found in this area proving that{the Endrick valley was formed by {ice}and the resulting lake stretched as far upstream as Fintry.
